<HEAD>Five Dead, 30 Injured When Bus Overturns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BILBAO, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus carrying West German and Portuguese
nationals veered off a highway and rolled into a ravine today,
killing five people and injuring 30, police said.
   The names and nationalities of the dead and injured were not
immediately known, but the official said most were West Germans or
Portuguese.
   He said the injured had been taken to six hospitals in Vizcaya
and Alava provinces for treatment for a variety of injuries, most
of them serious.
   The white Mercedes bus with West German licence plates had been
near Altube, near this northern city, when it overturned, the
official said, speaking on condition of anonymity.
   Rescue workers took more than an hour to free all of the injured
from the wreckage, he said.
