<2ND_LINE>PM-Taiwan-Earthquake,0117</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Strong Earthquake Jolts Eastern Taiwan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A strong earthquake centered off the coast
of Taiwan shook the island early today, but there were no reports
of casualties or damage, the Central Weather Bureau said.
   The earthquake struck at 2:10 a.m. and registered 6.7 on the
Richter scale, the bureau said. The epicenter was at sea about 65
miles southeast of the coastal city of Ilan in eastern Taiwan.
   The tremor was felt in the capital, Taipei, where residents
reported their houses shook violently, the bureau said.
   The Richter scale measures ground motion as recorded on
seismographs. An earthquake of magnitude 6 can cause severe damage
in a populated area.
