<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Zaire-FerrySinking     08-20 0119</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Zaire-Ferry Sinking,0121</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ferry Sinks In Lake Tanganyika, More Than 50 Feared Dead</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KINSHASA, Zaire (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An overloaded ferry sank in Lake
Tanganyika, and more than 50 people were feared dead, Zaire naval
sources said Saturday.
   Little information on the sinking was available in the capital,
Kinshasa, 1,000 miles west of the lake.
   The sources said the ferry, which sank Wednesday, was owned by a
citizen of nearby Rwanda. They did not know where the ferry sank on
the lake or its route.
   The sources, speaking on condition of anonymity, said the ferry
may have gone down because it was overloaded. They had no word on
survivors or the number of people who were aboard the vessel.
</TEXT>
