<HEAD>Woman Completes Solo 10-Week Sailing Trip From Japan</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto FX1</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Japanese woman realized her childhood
ambition to sail across the Pacific Ocean when she steered her
yacht through the Golden Gate after nearly 10 weeks at sea in the
solo crossing.
   Kyoko Imakiire, a 23-year-old former city employee from
Kagoshima, Japan, was welcomed ashore Friday night by St. Francis
Yacht Club members and other onlookers.
   Asked why she undertook the trip, she laughed and gave a simple
answer through an interpreter: ``I wanted to cross the Pacific.''
   Imakiire's voyage on the 28-foot yacht ``Kairen Tarachine'' from
her home city covered about 6,800 miles, according to the Japanese
Consulate. She left on June 11.
   Imakiire plans to begin a return voyage in October and arrive
back in Kagoshima in late November.
