<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Crack-Churches     08-20 0316</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Crack-Churches,0326</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Churches Not Safe From Scourge Of Crack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Crack cocaine addicts desperate for money to
support their habits are breaking into already needy churches in
north Dade County and stealing everything from children's toys to
religious icons.
   Thirty-five churches in the county have been burglarized an
average of three times each this year.
   ``We are attributing 90 percent of these robberies to drug
addicts looking to turn over a quick buck on anything they can
steal for a piece of crack ... they don't care about the sacredness
of the church,'' said Metro Special Investigations Unit detective
Don White.
   Besides toys and religious articles, other items stolen have
included toilet paper, speakers, microphones, amplifiers, food,
typewriters, telephones, adding machines and yard tools.
   Most of the churches are within walking distance of crack
houses, White said, adding that the number might be even higher
than reported because many ministers have told him they fear their
insurance premiums will go up if they report burglaries.
   New Mount Zion Church has been hit 20 times this year, but
Deacon Danny Swain has reported only one.
   ``What can we do?'' Swain asked. ``Burglars break the windows,
and every time we replace one, they just break it again. That costs
about $100 to $200 each time.
   ``When the burglars hit the day-care center in June, they stole
toys and $200 worth of food and milk,'' he said. ``Can you imagine
stealing things that belong to children?''
   Deacon Herbert Long of Bethany Seventh-day Adventist said his
parishioners dug deep to put in a $3,500 alarm system in July, but
that cut into the church's limited resources.
   ``Before July, we had deacons taking turns in twos to sit up at
the church between 1 a.m. and 6 a.m. to see if they could spot the
thief,'' Long said. ``He would always strike afterward when the
deacons would leave.''
</TEXT>
