<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Bird Smuggling,0115</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Canadian Tourist Jailed For Bird Smuggling</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Canadian tourist was sentenced to two
years in prison for attempting to smuggle rare birds out of
Australia.
   Randall McBride, 31, was sentenced Friday. It was one of the
longest prison terms ever imposed for violation of wildlife
protection laws.
   McBride, of Shelbourne, near Toronto, was convicted of
attempting to smuggle out of the country 37 native Australian birds
with an estimated value of $400,000 on the black market.
   He also was convicted of importing foreign birds into Australia.
Customs officials at Sydney airport said they discovered in his
luggage plastic tubing containing three macaws and eight parakeets.
</TEXT>
