<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Nigeria-Rains     08-20 0095</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Nigeria-Rains,0097</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rains Claims 26 Lives</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Torrential rains left 26 people dead and
destroyed more than 100 homes in Borno state in northeastern
Nigeria, the News Agency of Nigeria reported.
   Heavy rains earlier claimed up to 50 lives in neighboring Kano
state and forced the partial collapse of a dam, the agency said
Friday.
   The news agency said 17 of the deaths in Borno state occurred
when buildings collapsed.
   Several West African countries have reported similar downpours,
from Senegal south to Cameroon. Burkina Faso and Cameroon both
reported several deaths.
</TEXT>
